-- Talbots Q3 same-store sales fall 7.9 percent
-- 
-- Thu Nov 8, 2007 8:04am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/08/us-talbots-sales-idUSWNAS135120071108

 

 (Reuters) - Talbots Inc TLB.N said on Thursday its quarterly sales at stores open at least a year fell 7.9 percent. 

 Hingham, Massachusetts-based Talbots said total sales for the fiscal third quarter ended November 3 fell to $556 million from $569 million a year earlier. Analysts on average were expecting revenue of $546.8 million for the quarter, according to Reuters Estimates. The company said it sees fourth-quarter loss of 5 cents to 10 cents a share, including items. (Reporting by Manish Gupta in Bangalore; Editing by Jarshad Kakkrakandy)